If we look at the solution, we note

52
00:03:51,433 --> 00:03:57,924
that if ω > 2π R/M

53
00:03:58,473 --> 00:04:01,312
the current will grow exponentially.

54
00:04:02,754 --> 00:04:07,162
This provides flux amplification,
and therefore, dynamo action.

55
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:12,811
We also note that if we now spin the disk
in the opposite direction

56
00:04:12,811 --> 00:04:15,840
such that ω now is negative,

57
00:04:16,303 --> 00:04:21,455
no dynamo is possible, since
an initial current will be damped.

58
00:04:22,178 --> 00:04:26,773
In this simple mechanical dynamo example,

59
00:04:26,773 --> 00:04:30,051
the success of the dynamo depends

60
00:04:30,051 --> 00:04:34,114
on the built-in axial asymmetry
of the system

61
00:04:34,114 --> 00:04:38,647
which in this case is provided
by the contorted shape

62
00:04:38,647 --> 00:04:41,224
that the wire that carries the electrons,

63
00:04:41,224 --> 00:04:44,641
-in this case, this would be
the equivalent of the plasma flow,-

64
00:04:44,641 --> 00:04:48,029
is wound around the axis of our system.

65
00:04:48,334 --> 00:04:53,070
This is kind of a troubling observation
for astrophysical objects,

66
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:57,171
since in general they possess
a very good symmetry.

67
00:04:57,695 --> 00:05:02,762
Somehow this suggests that in such bodies,
a dynamo process must be linked

68
00:05:02,762 --> 00:05:06,366
to some asymmetries
of their internal motion.

69
00:05:06,698 --> 00:05:10,585
This is very far from obvious,
how this is going to happen.

70
00:05:11,126 --> 00:05:15,584
There is absolutely no guarantee
that in a spherical rotating object,

71
00:05:15,584 --> 00:05:17,513
such as, for example, the Sun,

72
00:05:17,513 --> 00:05:22,169
the fluid, the plasma motion,
can drive a suitably contorted flow

73
00:05:22,169 --> 00:05:24,158
to provide a dynamo effect.

74
00:05:25,384 --> 00:05:28,262
These observations that we have just made

75
00:05:28,262 --> 00:05:33,477
were put on solid ground
by a few theorems on the dynamo action.

76
00:05:33,792 --> 00:05:38,505
The results of some of these theorems
are recalled here

77
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:41,181
without going into the demonstrations.

78
00:05:42,377 --> 00:05:48,094
For example,
in Cartesian coordinates (x,y,z)

79
00:05:48,745 --> 00:05:54,006
no field independent of the coordinate z
that vanishes at infinity

80
00:05:54,006 --> 00:05:56,550
can be maintained by a dynamo action.

81
00:05:56,938 --> 00:06:01,139
This is telling us that it is
impossible to generate

82
00:06:01,139 --> 00:06:03,421
a two-dimensional dynamo field.

83
00:06:04,043 --> 00:06:09,622
A consequence of this theorem
is that in a toroidal system,

84
00:06:09,622 --> 00:06:14,045
a purely toroidal flow
cannot maintain a dynamo.

85
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:18,610
Probably the most important
of all dynamo theorems

86
00:06:18,610 --> 00:06:22,394
is the <i>Cowling Anti-Dynamo Theorem</i>,

87
00:06:22,928 --> 00:06:28,038
that states that an axisymmetric
magnetic field vanishing at infinity

88
00:06:28,038 --> 00:06:31,457
cannot be maintained by a dynamo action.

89
00:06:32,416 --> 00:06:37,334
A consequence is that dynamos with
a high degree of symmetry do not work.

90
00:06:37,970 --> 00:06:42,778
In particular, we cannot achieve
a stationary axisymmetric dynamo,

91
00:06:42,778 --> 00:06:45,918
a stationary centrally symmetric dynamo,

92
00:06:45,918 --> 00:06:51,095
or dynamos whose velocity field
is restricted to a plane.

93
00:06:51,686 --> 00:06:56,728
The result is that a successful dynamo
has to be complicated,

94
00:06:57,284 --> 00:06:59,738
and so will be its analysis.

95
00:07:02,664 --> 00:07:07,522
Now let's come back to the Sun and let's
try to answer the following question:

96
00:07:07,673 --> 00:07:10,127
How does plasma flow in the Sun?

97
00:07:10,127 --> 00:07:14,103
Is the plasma flow sufficiently contorted

98
00:07:14,607 --> 00:07:17,534
such that a dynamo action can take place?

99
00:07:18,190 --> 00:07:23,256
Let's start from the observations
of the rotation of the solar surface.

100
00:07:24,270 --> 00:07:26,722
We know that the Sun rotates,

101
00:07:26,722 --> 00:07:32,059
and the equator of the Sun
rotates in approximately 25 days.

102
00:07:32,835 --> 00:07:37,485
If we move to larger latitude,
towards the north pole of the Sun,

103
00:07:37,485 --> 00:07:42,714
we can observe that the surface of the Sun
does not rotate as a solid body.

104
00:07:43,064 --> 00:07:45,099
It spins differentially.

105
00:07:45,359 --> 00:07:49,650
The Sun rotates faster at the equator
than at its poles.

106
00:07:50,154 --> 00:07:55,584
While the equator needs approximately
25 days for a full revolution,

107
00:07:55,584 --> 00:07:59,504
the regions near the poles
will need about 31 days.

108
00:08:00,463 --> 00:08:03,468
This observation
shouldn't come as a surprise,

109
00:08:03,468 --> 00:08:06,454
since the Sun is not
a solid body like Earth,

110
00:08:06,454 --> 00:08:09,291
but is instead a huge sphere of plasma

111
00:08:09,291 --> 00:08:12,491
and different parts of it
can rotate at different speeds.

112
00:08:14,779 --> 00:08:19,698
Now, what about
the rotation inside the Sun?

113
00:08:20,324 --> 00:08:23,566
We cannot directly look
through the surface of the Sun

114
00:08:23,566 --> 00:08:27,931
since the plasma is opaque,
except for a thin layer,

115
00:08:27,931 --> 00:08:29,396
which is the photosphere.

116
00:08:29,687 --> 00:08:33,912
For this reason, the rotation
in the interior has remained a mystery

117
00:08:33,912 --> 00:08:37,751
until the recent development
of helioseismography.

118
00:08:38,108 --> 00:08:43,068
These consist in measuring the properties
of acoustic waves which propagate,

119
00:08:43,068 --> 00:08:45,216
are reflected and refracted,

120
00:08:45,216 --> 00:08:48,027
due to the variation of the material
where they propagate.

121
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:52,170
The analysis of the mode structures,
and the frequency of the waves

122
00:08:52,170 --> 00:08:56,573
allows us to determine how the rotation
varies within the depth of the Sun.

123
00:08:57,921 --> 00:09:01,614
The most recent observations
from helioseismic data

124
00:09:01,614 --> 00:09:06,087
are shown in this figure, which displays
the toroidal rotation frequency

125
00:09:06,310 --> 00:09:09,808
as a function of the radius
for different latitudes.

126
00:09:10,418 --> 00:09:13,735
Zero degrees corresponds
to the Sun's equator.

127
00:09:14,561 --> 00:09:17,735
We observe that in the inner
part of the Sun

128
00:09:17,735 --> 00:09:22,401
for R approximately
smaller than 0.7 R₀

129
00:09:22,401 --> 00:09:25,083
the Sun rotates as a rigid body

130
00:09:25,083 --> 00:09:28,841
at a speed between the polar
and the equatorial surface speeds.

131
00:09:33,096 --> 00:09:37,527
The transition to a constant rotation rate
happens in a very narrow region

132
00:09:37,527 --> 00:09:41,694
of a thickness 4% of the Sun's radius

133
00:09:41,694 --> 00:09:43,848
which is called the <i>tachocline</i>.

134
00:09:46,505 --> 00:09:51,261
In this region, the toroidal plasma flow
is extremely sheared

135
00:09:51,261 --> 00:09:54,758
since the changes happen
in a very narrow region

136
00:09:54,758 --> 00:09:58,414
and this differential rotation
can have important consequences

137
00:09:58,414 --> 00:10:02,260
for the magnetic field generation
as we will see later.

138
00:10:03,996 --> 00:10:08,888
Recently helioseismography
has revealed the presence of flows

139
00:10:08,888 --> 00:10:13,086
along the meridian lines
from the equator towards the pole

140
00:10:13,086 --> 00:10:18,475
at the Sun's surface, and from the poles
towards the equator below the surface.

141
00:10:19,745 --> 00:10:23,678
This is the so-called
<i>meridional circulation</i>.

142
00:10:26,771 --> 00:10:31,295
Near the surface, the flow
from the Equator to the North Pole

143
00:10:31,295 --> 00:10:34,003
is of the order of 20 meters per second.

144
00:10:35,384 --> 00:10:37,086
Slightly deeper in the Sun,

145
00:10:37,086 --> 00:10:41,184
the return flow from the North Pole
toward the Equator

146
00:10:41,184 --> 00:10:46,199
is much slower, with a speed of the order
of one to two meters per second.

147
00:10:47,806 --> 00:10:50,946
It is interesting to note
that this low flow return

148
00:10:50,946 --> 00:10:54,484
would carry material
from mid latitudes to the Equator

149
00:10:54,484 --> 00:10:56,423
in about 11 years,

150
00:10:56,423 --> 00:10:59,809
which is an important number
in solar cycle.

151
00:11:02,068 --> 00:11:05,545
So far we have seen
that the plasma in the Sun

152
00:11:05,545 --> 00:11:10,226
is characterized by the presence
of magnetic fields and plasma flows.

153
00:11:10,667 --> 00:11:11,911
How can we describe it?

154
00:11:12,369 --> 00:11:16,468
The key equation to describe the dynamics
of magnetic fields in a plasma

155
00:11:16,468 --> 00:11:20,377
is the induction equation
of the magnetohydrodynamics,

156
00:11:20,377 --> 00:11:21,873
which is shown here.

157
00:11:22,567 --> 00:11:25,941
In this equation, B represents
the magnetic field,

158
00:11:25,941 --> 00:11:27,836
v is the plasma flow,

159
00:11:32,645 --> 00:11:35,384
and σ is the plasma conductivity.

160
00:11:36,688 --> 00:11:41,995
This term, usually represented
with the letter λ ,

161
00:11:41,995 --> 00:11:46,100
is the magnetic diffusivity,
and in SI units

162
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:49,016
it is measured in m²/s .

163
00:11:50,932 --> 00:11:55,254
If we know the plasma flow
and we know the velocity v,

164
00:11:55,294 --> 00:11:58,472
this equation provides
the evolution of the magnetic field

165
00:11:58,472 --> 00:12:00,699
under some initial conditions.

166
00:12:02,024 --> 00:12:06,159
We can identify two contributions
to the variation of the magnetic field.

167
00:12:06,927 --> 00:12:11,508
The first term describes
a diffusion process

168
00:12:11,508 --> 00:12:14,370
which is produced
by the conductivity of the plasma.

169
00:12:14,795 --> 00:12:17,296
The second term
is a convection term

170
00:12:17,296 --> 00:12:19,659
and is produced
by the bulk plasma motion

171
00:12:19,659 --> 00:12:21,385
with the velocity v.

172
00:12:22,963 --> 00:12:24,671
Let's assume that B

173
00:12:24,671 --> 00:12:29,822
varies over a spatial scale
L and a temporal scale τ.

174
00:12:30,705 --> 00:12:34,858
Let's now consider the MHD
induction equation

175
00:12:34,858 --> 00:12:37,139
only with the diffusion term.

