Since we have ignored the advection term,

179
00:12:49,231 --> 00:12:53,138
this resisted diffusion time
will provide the timescale

180
00:12:53,306 --> 00:12:56,599
over which the magnetic field changes

181
00:12:56,599 --> 00:12:58,667
if diffusion dominates.

182
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:02,380
Let's now consider only the advection term

183
00:13:02,380 --> 00:13:03,923
and ignore diffusion.

184
00:13:03,923 --> 00:13:09,964
We can use the induction equation
and estimate the advection time this way.

185
00:13:11,417 --> 00:13:14,425
The advection time that we have estimated

186
00:13:14,425 --> 00:13:19,386
provides the timescale over which
the magnetic field would change

187
00:13:19,610 --> 00:13:22,814
if advection dominates the process.

188
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:29,114
How can we decide whether diffusion or
advection dominates the plasma dynamics?

189
00:13:32,037 --> 00:13:35,600
We can take the ratio of the two times

190
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:38,628
and use the expression
that we have just computed

